On the Mac, the build procedure should no longer require library -lg2c. 
  If it does for you, this probably indicates you are using an older 
version of Cantera.  If so, the best thing to do is to get the latest 
version from CVS.  Workarounds: try editing the Makefile and see if 
removing &quot;-lg2c&quot; works; or install the gnu Fortran 77 compiler, which 
will automatically install &quot;lg2c&quot; on your system.


